🔹 Step 1: Open the New Start Menu
Press Windows Key or click the center icon on taskbar


👉 You will notice:
Start Menu is centered
No live tiles
Pinned apps + Recommended section


🔹 Step 2: Explore the Centered Taskbar
Look at bottom of screen

👉 Changes:

Icons are in center
New icons (Start, Search, Widgets)
🔹 Step 3: Use Snap Layouts (Multitasking)
Open any window
Hover on maximize button

👉 You will see:

Layout options (split screen)
Choose layout → windows adjust automatically
🔹 Step 4: Open Widgets Panel
Press Windows + W

👉 You’ll get:

Weather 🌦️
News 📰
Calendar 📅
🔹 Step 5: Open New File Explorer
Press Windows + E

👉 Notice:

Clean toolbar
Icons instead of text
Tabs support
🔹 Step 6: Check Quick Settings & Notifications
Click on WiFi / Sound / Battery icon

👉 You’ll see:

Quick controls (WiFi, Bluetooth)
Separate notification panel
🔹 Step 7: Open Settings App (New UI)
Press Windows + I

👉 Changes:

Sidebar navigation
Clean design
🔹 Step 8: Try Virtual Desktops
Press Windows + Tab

👉 You can:

Add new desktops
Rename them
Set different wallpapers
